8. Functional Requirements (detailed)
- Ingestion
  - `/upload` API: accept PDF, return ingestion id; store original in `storage/`.
  - Extraction job: extract text pages, run OCR if needed, normalize whitespace.
  - Chunking: consistent chunk size (e.g., 500 tokens / 200–800 characters) with overlap and per-chunk source pointers (file, page, begin/end offsets).
- Embedding & Indexing
  - Batch embeddings with concurrency limits; retry on transient embedding-provider errors.
  - Store embeddings in Vector DB with chunk-level metadata.
- Search & QA
  - `/query` API: accepts query and optional doc filter; returns ranked answers, top-K chunks (with similarity scores) and synthesized answer with provenance.
  - Provide `explain` flag to surface underlying chunks and confidence scores for audit.
- User Management & Security
  - JWT-based auth for API and simple session for UI.
  - Per-user / per-tenant isolation for indexes and storage.

9. Non-Functional Requirements
- Security
  - TLS everywhere; secrets in environment variables and vault-compatible storage.
  - At-rest encryption for stored files and DB (as supported by host).
  - Audit logs for ingestion and query operations.
- Performance & Reliability
  - Horizontal worker scaling; instrument ingress/egress metrics.
  - Graceful retry/backoff for external providers.
- Observability
  - Health endpoints, ingestion queue metrics, index size, and query latency histograms.

10. Data & Privacy
- Retention: configurable per-org; default 90 days for temp indexes unless user marks persistent.
- Deletion: support immediate purge of docs and associated vectors on user request.

11. API Surface (examples)
- POST `/api/v1/upload` — multipart `file`; returns `{ ingestion_id }`.
- GET `/api/v1/ingestion/{id}` — ingestion status and logs.
- POST `/api/v1/query` — `{ q: string, doc_id?: string, top_k?: number }` → `{ answer, sources: [{doc, page, snippet, score}], raw_chunks }`.

